name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Quarantined]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection quarantined a virus or a security risk.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Cleaned]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection cleaned a virus or a security risk without deletion.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Deleted]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection deleted an object, such as a file or a registry key, to remove a risk.

query: class=symantec_endpoint_protection action=`cleaned by deletion` NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Cleaned By Deletion]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection cleaned a virus or a security risk via deletion.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Access Denied]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection Auto-Protect prevented a file from being created.

query: class=symantec_endpoint_protection action=`all actions failed` NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [All Remediation Actions Failed]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection's primary and secondary actions for the risk could not be executed. The risk may still be present on the system.

query: class=symantec_endpoint_protection action=`process terminate pending restart` NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Process Termination Pending Restart]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated a computer needs to be restarted to terminate a process to mitigate a risk.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Remediation Action Invalid]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated that an action it tried to take was invalid. These risks may still be present on the computer.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Remediation Details Pending]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated that it started a remediation process that has not completed.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Moved Back]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated that a user restored a file from quarantine.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Excluded]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated a user chose to exclude a security risk from detection. For example, this action can occur when a user is prompted for permission to terminate a process.

query: class=symantec_endpoint_protection action=`no repair available` NOT srcipv4:$exclusions.global.srcipv4
name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [No Repair Available]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated a risk was detected but no repair is available for the side effects of this risk.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Risk Partially Repaired]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated it cannot completely repair the effects of a virus or security risk.

name: SYMANTEC ENDPOINT PROTECTION [Unspecified Engine Failure]
description: Symantec Endpoint Protection indicated an engine failure occurred for an unspecified reason. These risks may still be present on the computer.
